{
  "texts": [
    "Financial data generation spans official reporting (formal documentation mandated by regulations) and usergenerated content (social media, customer chats).",
    "Annotation might be done by subject matter experts (e.g., compliance officers labeling risk factors), professional analysts (e.g., rating agencies), crowd workers (e.g., annotator labeling), or machines (e.g., AI labeling services).",
    "The expertise needed often correlates with the data's complexity-highly technical documents (e.g., derivative contracts) demand specialized annotators to ensure label accuracy.",
    "Annotations may be partially or fully automated, leveraging pattern-matching or prior language models to reduce costs.",
    "\"Language used for data/annotations?\""
  ]
}